[Table:Medical treatment]

The following persons are exempted from paying the visa fee:
An Applicant is eligible for visa fee exemption, if he/she fall under the below mentioned categories and submits a valid proof for the same:
- close relatives: spouse, children (including adopted), parents (guardians), grandparents and grandchildren of Ukrainian citizens that legally resides in EU and EU citizens –as a valid
                                                                            proof it is required to submit marriage certificate / birth certificate;
- the state members of the official delegations according to the official invitations that were addressed to the Ukrainian side, regularly participates in meetings, consultations, negotiations
                                                                            or an exchanging programs as well as in events that have been held by the intergovernmental organizations in Member States;
- the members of governments and parliament, the constitutional tribunals and Supreme Courts in case if they are not exempted of getting a visa according to this Agreement during theirterms
                                                                            of duties;
- pupils, students and teachers accompanying to them for a study or practice;
- Disabled and, if it is necessary, accompanying them guardians, in case submitting a valid proof for the same;
- persons which have presented the evidence that confirms the necessity to travel for a humanitarian reasons, urgent medical treatment with the accompanying persons; in purpose to attend
                                                                            the funeral of close relative or to visit seriously ill relative;
- the participants in an international sports events and persons accompanying to them;
- the participants in activities: scientific, cultural artistic as well as university or other exchanging programs;
- the participants in an official exchanging programs that are organized by the twin cities;
- journalists;
- retired persons by age*
- drivers carrying the goods in the international traffic, drivers of the passengers' transports travelling to EU by the vehicles that were registered in Ukraine;
- the members of the train, refrigerator and locative crews in an international trips that are going to the territories of the Member States;
- Children under 18 years and children under 21 years which are kept by their parents or students under 21 years providing the valid students card (original and copy) and original of
                                                                            statement from the University.
- representatives of religious communities;
- representatives of liberal professions taking part in international exhibitions, conferences, symposia, seminars or other similar events heldin the territory of the Member States;
- people aged under 25 participating in seminars, conferences, sports, cultural or educational events organized by non-profit organizations;
- representatives of civil society organizations traveling for the purpose of participating in training, seminars and conferences, including in the framework of exchange programs;
- participants in official European Union cross-border cooperation programs, such as the European Neighborhood and Partnership Instrument.
Please Note: 
- Visa fee and VFS service charge can be paid at the visa application centre in cash, through credit or debit card and are non-refundable.
- Visa and service fees needs to be paid in UAH only.

